<br>
Take our control over &quot;Summoned&quot; creatures.  Every class that has some kind of tie-in with a type of mob (Animal and Undead mostly) gets some spells to help them with that type of mob.  We get a line of damage to summoned spells.  Great.  Druids (and, to a lesser degree, Shamans and Rangers) can Charm, Mezz, Fear and be Invis to Animals.  Necros can Charm, Mezz, Fear and be Invis to Undead, and Clerics, Paladins and Shadowknights get some of these abilities as well.<br>
<br>
So why in the heck don't we get anything like this for summoned creatures?  Would it really be all that unbalancing for us to be able to Charm, Mezz, Fear or get Invis Vs. Summoned?  As a normal extension of our class's abilities, I don't understand why we haven't been given ANY of this.  It's certainly not unbalancing, especially since there is a very small number of areas in the game where you can even find &quot;Summoned&quot; mobs.<br>
<br>
Then there's the Elemental Illusions...  Can somebody PLEASE explain to me why we don't get these?  I won't even go into a long tirade about why we deserve them.  It goes without saying.  I'll just bitch and moan about it instead.  Well actually, I don't need to do that either.  You get the point.  Not giving these spells to us (When those damnable Necromancers get Skeleton illusion) is just plain idiotic.<br>
<br>
Let's not forget improved invisibility.  Umm, why are we the only caster that doesn't get this one?<br>
<br>
Mana regen...  same deal there, all the rest of the casters get it in some way.  Mod Rods are semi-useful, but basically only as a means of mana transfer and maybe as a one-shot &quot;One More Nuke To Save My Ass&quot; solution every once in awhile.  I'm not looking for clarity or even breeze, but some kinda Pet Health -&gt; My Mana deal would be not only useful but also in-character.<br>
<br>
But honestly...  I can live without root, I can live without snare, I can live without mana regen, I can live without bigass nukes and I can live without ports...  I just want to actually have as much control over the area that I'm SUPPOSED to be a master of as I should.  Most of all, I want my damn elemental illusions!<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
Oh well, at least I can summon beer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
