<br>
To me, being the &quot;Master of Elements&quot; doesn't mean that I can turn into a duplicate of my pet.  That is firmly in the realm of enchanters.  It doesn't mean that I can charm other conjured beings.  That would be the &quot;master of conjuration and conjured thingies&quot; :)(which is kind of what we are even though we don't have the title).<br>
<br>
Right now the only element we can manipulate directly is fire.  I don't know how conjuring blades qualifies as elements.  Being the &quot;Master of the Elements&quot; should give us the ability to do damage through each of the elements.  Instead of just DDs based on fire we should also have ice, wind and earth.  <br>
<br>
Or if they don't want us to have other DDs they could use thier imagination and implement other effects.  Imagine:<br>
<br>
Water - A freeze spell that operates more or less like screaming terror.  Bonus points if they can turn the Mobs transparent or make it look like it's covered in ice.<br>
Wind - Knockback and stun.  (Knocks a Mob out of the group(several feet) and stuns it for several seconds so another class can root it)<br>
Earth - creates a quagmire in a specific area that &quot;snares&quot; anything in it.  (Not sure they can do this but I imagine they can reuse code from the enchanters sentinal spell) <br>
<br>
In summary...getting illusions won't make us masters of the elements, getting spells that allow us to do things BASED on the elements will.<br>
